{"title_page": "Christopher Hawthorne (journalist)", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|text=American screenwriter and producer [[Christopher Hawthorne]]}}\n'''Christopher Hawthorne''' is an American journalist and television director who served as the architecture critic for the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' from 2004 to 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la.curbed.com/2018/3/13/17111610/christopher-hawthorne-interview-chief-design-officer|title=Critic Christopher Hawthorne explains why he\u2019s taking a job with the city|first=Alissa|last=Walker|date=March 13, 2018|website=Curbed LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hyperallergic.com/433134/los-angeles-christopher-hawthorne-chief-design-officer/|title=Why the City of Los Angeles Hired a \"Chief Design Officer\"|date=March 27, 2018|website=Hyperallergic}}</ref> In 2018, Los Angeles Mayor [[Eric Garcetti]] appointed him as the city's first Chief Design Officer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theoccidentalnews.com/features/2019/02/19/as-las-first-chief-design-officer-professor-christopher-hawthorne-is-the-man-behind-the-future-of-the-city/2896404|title=As LA\u2019s first Chief Design Officer, professor Christopher Hawthorne is the man behind the future of the city|first=Pablo|last=Nukaya-Petralia|date=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, he directed the documentary ''That Far Corner'' for the [[KCET]] series ''[[Artbound]]'' about architect [[Frank Lloyd Wright]]'s work in Los Angeles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/that-far-corner-frank-lloyd-wright-los-angeles|title=What Do These Frank Lloyd Wright Houses Have to Do With a 1914 Murder?|first=Cond\u00e9|last=Nast|website=Architectural Digest}}</ref> He also directed another ''Artbound'' episode titled ''Third Los Angeles''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://la.curbed.com/2016/6/14/11938840/video-third-los-angeles|title=Take a Tour of the Third Los Angeles|first=Bianca|last=Barragan|date=June 14, 2016|website=Curbed LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ww